In England, in the seven days to 11 March, there were 328,120 new confirmed cases (580.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 04 March, there were 198,643 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 65% (129,477 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 16 March is 16,785,149 (29,681.9 cases per 100,000 population).
